modules.description: Supports operations for structured logging, including configurable severity levels (FATAL, ERROR, WARN, INFO, DEBUG), color-coded terminal output, and customizable message prefixes with built-in timestamp integration. Works with log_level enumerations, color specifications, and output destinations to enable real-time monitoring with visual severity differentiation or generating contextualized logs for debugging and auditing workflows.

Structured logging with configurable severity levels, color-coded output, and customizable message prefixes including timestamps. Supports log levels like FATAL, ERROR, WARN, INFO, DEBUG, and integrates with terminal displays or file outputs. Useful for real-time monitoring, debugging, and audit logging with visual severity cues.
